Process called "create_initial_simplex" that takes x0 as NDArray.NDArray returns List[NDArray.NDArray]:
    Let n_vars be x0.size
    Let simplex be list containing
    Add NDArray.copy_array with arr as x0 to simplex For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
    Let vertex be NDArray.copy_array with arr as x0
    Set vertex.data at index i to vertex.data at index i 0.1
    Add vertex to simplex Return simplex

Process called "evaluate_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] returns List[Float]:
    Let values be list containing
    For each vertex in simplex:
    Add func with vertex to values
    Return values

Process called "sort_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and values as List[Float]:
    Note: Simple bubble sort
    Let n be Collections.List.length with lst as simplex
    For i from 0 to n - 2:
    For j from 0 to n - 2 - i:
    If values at index j is greater than values at index (j 1):
    Let temp_vertex be simplex at index j
    Set simplex at index j to simplex at index (j 1)
    Set simplex at index (j 1) to temp_vertex Let temp_value be values at index j
    Set values at index j to values at index (j 1)
    Set values at index (j 1) to temp_value

Process called "compute_simplex_centroid" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and n_points as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let first_vertex be simplex at index 0
    Let centroid be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing first_vertex.size For i from 0 to n_points - 1:
    Let vertex be simplex at index i
    For j from 0 to vertex.size - 1:
    Set centroid.data at index j to centroid.data at index j vertex.data at index j For j from 0 to centroid.size - 1:
    Set centroid.data at index j to centroid.data at index j divided by Float.from with value as n_points Return centroid

Process called "reflect_point" that takes point as NDArray.NDArray and centroid as NDArray.NDArray and alpha as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let direction be vector_subtract with a as centroid and b as point
    Return vector_add with a as centroid and b as vector_scale with vector as direction and scalar as alpha

Process called "shrink_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and values as List[Float] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float]:
    Let best_vertex be simplex at index 0
    For i from 1 to Collections.List.length with lst as simplex - 1:
    Let vertex be simplex at index i
    Let shrunk_vertex be vector_add with a as best_vertex and b as vector_scale with vector as vector_subtract with a as vertex and b as best_vertex and scalar as 0.5
    Set simplex at index i to shrunk_vertex
    Set values at index i to func with shrunk_vertex

