Process called "create_merit_function" that takes objective as ObjectiveFunction and constraints as List[ConstraintFunction] and penalty as Float returns Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float]:
    Return function that takes x as NDArray.NDArray returns Float: Return objective.function with x

Process called "initialize_random_population" that takes bounds as List[Tuple[Float, Float]] and size as Integer returns List[NDArray.NDArray]:
    Let population be list containing
    Let n_vars be Collections.List.length with lst as bounds For i from 0 to size - 1:
    Let individual be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
    Let bound be bounds at index j
    Let lower be bound.first
    Let upper be bound.second
    Let value be lower (upper - lower) multiplied by 0.5
    Set individual.data at index j to value
    Add individual to population Return population

Process called "evaluate_population" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] returns List[Float]:
    Let fitness be list containing
    For each individual in population:
    Add func with individual to fitness
    Return fitness

Process called "get_best_individual" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and fitness as List[Float] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let best_index be 0
    Let best_fitness be fitness at index 0 For i from 1 to Collections.List.length with lst as fitness - 1:
    If fitness at index i is less than best_fitness:
    Set best_index to i
    Set best_fitness to fitness at index i Return population at index best_index

Process called "get_best_fitness" that takes fitness as List[Float] returns Float:
    Let best be fitness at index 0
    For each f in fitness:
    Set best to Math.min with a as best and b as f
    Return best

Process called "create_mutant_vector" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and target_index as Integer and F as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_vars be (population at index 0).size
    Let mutant be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars Note: Simple mutation - just copy target for now
    Return NDArray.copy_array with arr as population at index target_index

Process called "crossover_vectors" that takes target as NDArray.NDArray and mutant as NDArray.NDArray and CR as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let trial be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing target.size
    For i from 0 to target.size - 1:
    If 0.5 is less than CR:
    Set trial.data at index i to mutant.data at index i
    Otherwise:
    Set trial.data at index i to target.data at index i
    Return trial

Process called "apply_bounds_to_vector" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray and bounds as List[Tuple[Float, Float]] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let bounded_vector be NDArray.copy_array with arr as vector
    For i from 0 to vector.size - 1:
    Let bound be bounds at index i
    Let value be Float.from with value as vector.data at index i
    Let clamped_value be Math.max with a as bound.first and b as Math.min with a as bound.second and b as value
    Set bounded_vector.data at index i to clamped_value
    Return bounded_vector

Process called "calculate_population_diversity" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] returns Float:
    Return 1.0

Process called "calculate_sum_of_squares" that takes residuals as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq be 0.0
    For i from 0 to residuals.size - 1:
    Let r be Float.from with value as residuals.data at index i
    Set sum_sq to sum_sq r multiplied by r
    Return sum_sq

Process called "compute_least_squares_gradient" that takes jacobian as NDArray.NDArray and residuals as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: J^T multiplied by r
    Let n_vars be jacobian.shape at index 1
    Let gradient be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    Return gradient

Process called "compute_gauss_newton_hessian" that takes jacobian as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: J^T multiplied by J
    Let n_vars be jacobian.shape at index 1
    Return create_identity_matrix with size as n_vars

Process called "add_diagonal_damping" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and damping as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let augmented be NDArray.copy_array with arr as matrix
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
    Let current_val be Float.from with value as augmented.data at index (i multiplied by n i)
    Set augmented.data at index (i multiplied by n i) to current_val damping
    Return augmented

